    {
      "front": "Why is eBGP AD (20) lower than OSPF (110)?",
      "back": "Cisco trusts inter-AS BGP peers over IGP routes when both learn the same prefix \u2014 eBGP routes are more specific to external reachability.",
      "tags": "flashcards/administrative-distance"
    },
    {
      "front": "Why is iBGP AD (200) higher than every IGP?",
      "back": "Inside an AS, you want the IGP to win and route packets internally \u2014 iBGP just carries reachability, not optimal IGP paths.",
      "tags": "flashcards/administrative-distance"
